############################################################################################################
# This configuration file is so that you can easily enable adhoc firewall ports if you need ports to be open
# that aren't open in the default configurations for an application need. Say, for example you modified the 
# scripts to support phpmyadmin then you might want port 8080 to be open to your ip addres 81.10.166.111/32
# on your webserver so to achieve that you would put this line into this file 
#
# WEBSERVERPORTS:8080|ipv4|81.10.166.111/32
#
# if your application had some further need that additionally required port 1111 to be open to all machines 
# you would use:
#
# WEBSERVERPORTS:8080|ipv4|81.10.166.111/32 1111|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
#
# as long as you follow this exact format the webserver machine and the firewall of your provider will
# be automatically configured to reflect this configurations and the ports defined will be open.
# You can only set one configuration set active at a time and you do that by uncommenting it as you can see
# from the default set. If you are trying different webserver combinations you will likely need to visit
# this file each time you change your configuration to, for example, include or exclude reverse proxies.
# REMEMBER: if you are using a loadbalancer you will most likely want your reverse proxies that the loadbalancer
# forwards traffic to completely firewalled off from the public internet allowing the loadbalancer to be the
# public face of your webproperty. 
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 1: This is the firewall configuration you use when you want your webservers to be accessible
# from any IP address on the Internet and is the default configuration for the quick demos
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0 
#DATABASEPORTS:
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 2: This is the firewall configuration you use when you want your webservers to be accessible
# only from cloudflare ip addresses and you are not using an authentication server
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:443|ipv4|cloudflare
#DATABASEPORTS:
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 3: This is the firewall configuration you use when you want your reverse proxy servers to be
# accessible from any ip address on the Internet and you are not using an authentication server
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0 
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:
#DATABASEPORTS:
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 4: This is the firewall configuration you use when you want your reverse proxies to be accessible
# only from cloudflare ip addresses and you are not using an authentication server
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:443|ipv4|cloudflare 
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:
#DATABASEPORTS:
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 5: This is the firewall configuration you use when you are using an authentication server
# that you are using to allow access by "basic auth" to the reverse proxy 
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0 
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:
#DATABASEPORTS:
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 6: This is the firewall configuration you use when you are using an authentication server
# that you using to allow access by "basic auth" to the reverse proxy that is accessible from cloudflare
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:443|ipv4|cloudflare  
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:
#DATABASEPORTS:
############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 7: This is the firewall configuration you use when you are using an authentication server
# that you using to allow access by "firewall" to the reverse proxy 
#############################################################################################################
#AUTHENTICATORPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0  
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:
#AUTOSCALERPORTS:
#WEBSERVERPORTS:
#DATABASEPORTS:


############################################################################################################
# CONFIGURATION 8: This is the firewall configuration you use when you are using an authentication server
# that you using to allow access by "wireguard" to the proxy machine. Access to the proxy is controlled using
# wireguard and then the websever(s) only accept requests that originate from our wireguard accssible proxy
# machines. This means that our webservers are not world accessible (no world open 443 port) and our proxy machines 
# are only accessible via our wireguard authentication process. This makes it very hard for bots and so to probe
# any of your machines although it might take a bit of understanding to see how this works on your part
# The wirguard port is "SSH_PORT + 1" so here it is set to 1036 because I set SSH_PORT to 1035 if you have set
# a different SSH_PORT then you will need to change the 1036 value on your proxy machine. If your SSH_PORT is
# set to 2078 then you would need to set:
# REVERSEPROXYPORTS:2079|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
# Of course this looks like its world accessible based on the firewall settings but actually the access is controlled by 
# crpyptokey routing rather than the firewall. So, anyone without an appropriate crypto key will not be able to access
# this port
# Similarly:
# WEBSERVERPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
# Allows access through the native firewall but the operating system firewall (ufw or iptables) will block all ip
# addresses except the ip addresses of our proxy machines behind the scenes and so for this to work your native
# firewall and your OS firewall (ufw or iptables) both have to be activated.
#############################################################################################################
AUTHENTICATORPORTS:443|ipv4|cloudflare  
#REVERSEPROXYPORTS:1036|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
REVERSEPROXYPORTS:
AUTOSCALERPORTS:
WEBSERVERPORTS:443|ipv4|0.0.0.0/0
DATABASEPORTS:





